rComments: Lots of articles to read and give summaries of them every week, so participation in classes matters. He is not good in answering students' questions and is not clear in lectures. I expected hormones and behaviour (psy395)  to cover a broad subject, but he only talked about sexual behaviour (his field of research). Would not take again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: You really feel the science behind psych. Paper readings helped develop better sense of the course, even though a bit annoying, looking back it was great. He tests on lecture - no book, so attendance mandatory. He's interested and gives nice facts and very knowledgeable and helpful! I had fun

I personally enjoyed his teaching style. He doesn't test anything he hasn't talked about in class. He's interested in the topic & the subject itself is interesting. I went to every lecture, not only for participation marks, but also because it was fun and interesting. Small class size bonus , the poster presentation was straight forward. Loved it!
Super great prof. most fair course i have taken at utm. loved the small lecture style!
Avoid this prof.  Unfriendly, unhelpful and unclear in class.

The class has no structure whatsoever. It is rushed and there isn't enough equipment for everyone. Monks is terrible at answering questions unless you're discussing a very specific concept (yes, his name is Monks not Monk). But the man is quite handsome (the photo here is outdated, google it) so that was some consolation for his teaching.
The course material itself was interesting but the tests were extremely hard. Marking was ambiguous. Avoid this course if possible.
Does not explain anything. Useless.

There is way too much information in this class to properly cover over half a semester, it should be a full year course like the physiology in second year bio. I could have seen myself getting so  much out of a class like this, but mainly everything is rushed and you drown in all of the information.

I attended class once, so I don't have enough to say about him except that I already sent him my fifth email on the term paper, asking for instructions, and he still hasn't responded to my message!  I guess I have to attend his office hr & see for myself how rude he really is.  Read book thoroughly in order to do well in tests.  He's not hot to me.

2nd worst proff I have had by far. Reads off the slides. Does not tell you any new info that is not already on textbook. He is rude and ambiguous, specially when talking about the paper. He DOES NOT GIVE ANY INFO about the paper, only bits and pieces in class. DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE. Take PSY295 instead.

I don't know why everyone is complaining... I had him for PSY290 and it was fine. It's a memory-intensive course, though. You have to read the textbook cover-to-cover and go to class, as he asks questions like "as discussed in lecture..." The stuff from "boxes" in the text is also important. The essay was the worst part of the course!
Please don't rate him based on his looks, it's more useful to us otherwise. He goes extremely fast, can't understand a word he says...zooms by. I am considering dropping the course.

This prof is very rude. At first I thought he was kinda cute, but then I spoke to him in person and he was so mean. I didn't think he was cute after that. He was really mean. I guess he must be really smart with research because he's just not a good teacher. He mumbles a lot, I've never seen him smile, not once and I guess he doesnt like students.

I studied EVERY DETAIL for my first test & got 33%. Shocked, I went to his office wondering if there was a mistake. He was condescending and rude. He said my study strategies must have been poor. He said the TAs don't make mistakes and "better luck next time." 3 weeks later I got an email saying there was a mistake in the grading & my mark was 77%.

Monotonous lecturer; less monotonous if talking abt smt he likes. Most of what was in the lecture was also in the txt, some was not. Must attend lectures + read text to do well. & memorize all the little details, the different brain pathways associated with specific neurotransmitters, etc. The tests this yr were all MC. I liked the course though.
content for course interesting. However, tests were hard....really hard :(

His tests, even if you were to study for months, are impossible to do well on. He asks useless questions, most of while are based on irrelevant statistics from the textbook. If you are good at memorizing useless facts, take his class. If you are really interested in learning, avoid him like the plague!
He's unbelievably daft.
Horrible professor. Would never take one of his courses again. Should not be teaching at University that requires so much from it's students.
Unhelpful. Rude. Condescending. Bad at teaching. Doesn't care about students. Lectures are useless. Tests are ambiguous and ask irrelevant questions.
Horrible prof. Really unhelpful and causes students to completely loose faith. I wouldn't suggest taking any of his courses.

Horrible professor, I tried to go to him for help numerous times and he is very condescending. I realized that numerous students have already gone to the dean amount him, if you don't want your gpa to fall, don't take his course. Horrible prof and I regret talking his course deeply.
Pretty good prof

Very monotone voice. He decided that this yr the test would be half MC & thr other SA...which screwed our marks because the kept experimenting with tests...have to atttend both Lec & rd the book...no choice :(

I fell asleep in his class but managed an 80+ so attendance is not mandatory IMO. ADVICE: READ LECS AND TEXTBOOK THOROUGHLY & REPEATEDLY! If there are any numbers (eg. 20% population has a  mental disorder) are VERY IMPORTANT!! his test is all MC, and the exam is noncumulative, this is why his questions will be VERY specific!

not the best lecturer, repeats everything from the book with little added material to make anything interesting. Dont even need to really attend. The book is crucial however, and he tests you on the BOX 1.3 stuff also.
hes really boring to listen to in class..never attended a single lecture. his tests are okay..just know everything in the textbook and ull be fine

Course was pretty interesting, but the first test was brutal and unfair.  He did try to make up for it.  I didn't find him to be very clear when he was lecturing.  Without the slides, I'd probably wonder what the hell his point is.  He has improved, however, as I  had him two years ago when he was an even bigger noob prof, and he's gotten better.

When I spoke to him he was mean also, which surprised me because he seemed pretty reasonable and even socially awkward in lecture. I had a hard time figuring out how to study for the course, probably because his TAs make up the questions for his tests.

HE IS SOOOOOOOOOOOO HOT!!! His wife is damn lucky. Sometimes I couldnt pay attention cause I just wanted to look at him. He is understanding. and nice to look at, verynice to look at, so nice that he's a distraction. LOL. Nice to talk to, smart, sexy, everything good in one package. loved him, fair, and sexy as can be
He's a cool prof.  haha my firends took his course cause he's hot!  but i love the 10% participation thing he does and how he addresses questions at the beginning of the class.

He is a very intelligent man, and just as good loooking. He tries his best to engage all of us in the lecture through his strategy of handing of questions at the end of the class. I really liked that percent of the mark. His tests are fair... just know everyhting in the book. Finally, he makes it a very interesting and enjoyable course.

Oh man Ashley Monks, is by far one of the best professors UTM has to offer, let alone he's quite nice to look at lol. But you'll enjoy the class if you enjoy biology, he is amazing and so is the course. Lectures are clear, and come from the book, which I find helps. He also makes the funniest comments while lecturing. What an amazing guy!

Great prof, tries to make the lectures as interesting as he can. Material is pretty boring though, and you definately have to memorize entire chapters for the tests. Don't really like the "class participation" questions either. But overall it's a good course to take.
not only is ashley monks ****in hot, he's intelligent, geeky and funny... i enjoy the lectures from the text book.. it's easy. give the stuttering stanely a break for his boyish good looks;)
Monks is hilarious, this guy has the best sense of humour, and really tries to help his students succeed

LOL I'm not even taking this course - I sit in with a person I know that takes it, and I even like the course. I am definately taking it next year - he's a great prof! And he's also very understanding too. He has random slides with random things on it that makes us laugh, like listing X-Men's enemies. I can't wait til next year =]

Course layout is clear and material is easy.  Lectures are a complete waste of time, all he does is lecture the textbook (you can literally follow along), even his examples are from the book. Worse yet, he forces you to show up by making 10% of your mark based on questions handed in at the end of class...
boring lectures, reads straight off the powerpoint, and even then everything in his lecture notes is straight from the textbook! good looking man though
